      "raw_output": "SCORE: 2\nEXPLANATION: The vocabulary is sufficient for expressing ideas on a work-related topic (market analysis) with some business terminology (\"market share,\" \"purchasing power,\" \"competitive products,\" \"invest\"). However, there are noticeable errors and awkward formulations that indicate vocabulary gaps: \"prefer magazines than blogs\" (should be \"prefer magazines TO blogs\"), \"purchases at least a magazine month\" (missing \"a\" or \"per\"), \"The 15- to 19-year-old women group\" (awkward phrasing - better: \"female demographic\"), and \"the size of the males\" (should be \"male demographic/group\"). The writer shows limited ability to vary formulation, with repetition of \"purchasing power,\" \"increase,\" \"group,\" and \"period\" throughout. These errors and the lack of lexical variety indicate good control of elementary vocabulary but difficulties with more complex expression. Consistent with B1 vocabulary descriptors. CEFR level: B1.\nCONFIDENCE: 0.80",
